<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-454-837  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 454 837.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 26 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Igra-Tekhnika manages Moscow technopolis project, ATandamp;Tparticipates.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tchashchin, Kirill.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (planning).andO;Topic:     Igra-TechnikaSoviet UnionIndustry-Sponsored ResearchUrban Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IGRA-TEKHNIKA MANAGES MOSCOW TECHNOPOLIS PROJECT, ATandamp;T PARTICIPATES MOSCOW,U.S.S.R., 1990 JUL 11 (NB) -- ATandamp;T will participate in a proposed project tobuild a high-tech &quot;Island if the Future&quot; cosmopolis in Moscow, Leningrad andother Soviet cities.andM;According to Umuta Kemelbekova, project director and a vice-chairman of thecooperative amalgamation &quot;Igra-Technika&quot; (Game-Technics), their idea ofcosmopolis, which is not only a high-tech place but a learning center, haswon over several US businessmen who are looking to implement the concept inthe Soviet Union.andM;The Cosmopolis will include a big game-park, high-tech research centers,business and information structures, hotels and cultural places.andP;  It willalso include the first Institute of the Future in the USSR, another idea of&quot;Igra-Technika.&quot;andM;Kemelbekova told Newsbytes that the idea was accepted by Capital HillsDevelopment, involved in a 2,000 acre planned intelligent city near LosAngeles, CA.andP;  This company is ready to build a Moscow-based one also.andM;ATandamp;T, which is participating in the California development, will take part inMoscow project.andP;  Newsbytes has learned that this willbe ATandamp;T's firstparticipation in a project in the USSR.andP;  The company will supply fiber opticsand data switching equipment for data networking and teleconferencing.andP;  Plansinclude an earth station with satellite up-links through a teleport toprovide advanced video conferencing and high speed data transfer.andM;The technology-based city is expected to be built in Moscow although there'sno decision on land allocation or leasing yet.andP;  Despite the support at highlevels, the decision-making is very slow.andP;  Kemelbekova told Newsbytes thatother cities including Leningrad, Dnepropetrovsk and Donetsk are also willingto have cosmopolises and probably development will start in one of thesecities.andM;(Kirill Tchashchin/19900713/Press contact: Umuta Kemelbekova, Igra- Technika,phone +7 095 946-4551 fax +7 095 230-2787)</TEXT></DOC>